{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T03:40:59.960309883Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-59f47374","body":"In `src/adapters/fs.rs:2824-2851`, `read_controller_journal_from_path` fails hard on any malformed NDJSON line. Since the journal is the write-ahead source of truth and `append_line` writes separator + data non-atomically (lines 647-650), a crash mid-write could leave a truncated trailing line. This would make ALL controller operations fail permanently until the file is manually repaired. The reader should tolerate a malformed *final* line (log a warning and discard it) while still rejecting corruption in earlier lines, matching the write-ahead-log pattern where the last entry may be incomplete.","dedup_key":"29a1e30091eacee32cd544870f4b52623ea1425a78ee99a15d8091c08434401c","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T03:40:59.968811161Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-9f67b47b","body":"Add a test for `resume_controller` when the persisted state has a semantic validation failure (e.g., `Running` state with missing `active_task_id`). The code path at `controller.rs:465-475` transitions to `NeedsOperator` on validation failure (unless already in `NeedsOperator`), but no test exercises this branch. This is the core 'stale state detection' requirement from the acceptance criteria.","dedup_key":"aa558c3d9888540ea524f57b3e8fabb7e1331f3239605bfe5dcb4660106b5600","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":19,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T03:40:59.977078410Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-937c41bf","body":"Fix the invalid-state resume path in `src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:352-357`, `src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:411-412`, and `src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:465-474`. `resume_transition_request()` correctly classifies semantic validation failures as a `needs_operator` transition, but `resume_controller()` routes that request through `transition_from_current_locked()`, which immediately re-runs `current.validate_semantics()` and aborts before the recovery transition is journaled or persisted. A stale controller such as `running` without `active_task_id` still returns `CorruptRecord` instead of moving to `needs_operator`.","dedup_key":"7acdb9a53970f77eb44e032ae674f26bdb5eac7aeaae3c2efa598268604ffc04","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T03:40:59.985348674Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-666d8c32","body":"Tighten transition validation in `src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:437-455` and `src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:685-724` so in-flight transitions preserve the active bead/task identity unless the state machine is explicitly clearing it. Right now only the target state’s shape is checked, so `claimed`/`running`/`reconciling` can silently swap to a different bead or task; for example, `running(bead-a, task-1)` can transition to `reconciling(bead-b, task-2)` and be accepted as legal.","dedup_key":"b28c213e17c33508b286d936fbf5971ff855af6f776e28389dd6d03a88027e27","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
