{"sequence":37,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T04:03:36.203954237Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-2598860d","body":"In `src/adapters/fs.rs:2922-2936`, `FsMilestoneControllerStore::with_controller_lock` acquires the same `mutation_lock_path` as `FsMilestoneSnapshotStore::with_milestone_lock` but does not call `recover_pending_state_commit`. If a snapshot write was interrupted (leaving a pending state-commit sidecar), the controller lock acquisition won't clean it up. Add `FsMilestoneSnapshotStore::recover_pending_state_commit(base_dir, milestone_id)?;` after acquiring the lock in the controller's `with_controller_lock`, matching the snapshot store's pattern at line 2769.","dedup_key":"0967966d5eb51e2e21a3d05ecd9a066d410df10bd9e42d05e1aec9fa9bf1d296","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":38,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T04:03:36.212881013Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-92c9f2d8","body":"In `src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:275-300`, `initialize_controller_with_state` writes controller.json but does not append a journal event. If controller.json is lost (disk corruption, manual deletion) before any transition occurs, a non-Idle initial state is unrecoverable from the journal. Either emit a synthetic journal event on initialization (e.g., with from_state == to_state as a sentinel, or a dedicated 'initialized' event type), or document that initialization state is only recoverable from controller.json and that the journal alone is insufficient for pre-first-transition recovery.","dedup_key":"8afe870e71f96b5ab712a2cb30c46ec079d5ad53005aa6ded5159031e01d508f","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":39,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T04:03:36.221850950Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-8926fec5","body":"Wire the new controller into the real milestone execution path before merging. The new API lives in `src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:260-360`, but production start/reconcile code still updates milestone state exclusively through the old snapshot/lineage helpers in `src/cli/run.rs:272-283` and `src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:267-350`. As shipped, real runs never create or consult `controller.json` / `controller-journal.ndjson`, so stop/resume behavior is unchanged and the bead's persistence/resume acceptance criteria are not actually met.","dedup_key":"1c6117da031f4fbee79c73ad675fccf3798268ac1f8039f867858efee1f4ff61","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":40,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T04:03:36.230837509Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-388a7fb9","body":"Validate persisted controller snapshots on load. `load_controller()` returns whatever `hydrate_controller_locked()` gives it (`src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:302-400`), but that helper never calls `validate_semantics()` when `controller.json` is the only source of truth or when it already matches the last journal entry. `read_controller_from_path()` in `src/adapters/fs.rs:2797-2821` also accepts any `schema_version` and only checks `milestone_id`. A corrupt snapshot like `state=running` with no `active_task_id`, or a future incompatible schema version, will therefore be treated as a valid loaded controller until some later mutation happens to trip over it.","dedup_key":"1d80804dcc541d1189f50c491937492aa97d94b687b4117b04cb0af72a7007f2","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":41,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T04:03:36.239740961Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-298ae1fc","body":"Do not treat a persisted `running` controller as healthy when the runtime reports the task is still `Pending`. In the claimed-state resume branch, `Pending` means 'stay claimed' (`src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:542-547`), but in the running-state branch the same runtime status is treated as 'keep running' (`src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:569-580`). That leaves the controller in a semantically stale state after restart: the task has not started, but the controller still says it is running.","dedup_key":"d64ae1f17a5a1d7cd591bf8fc41c071f0cb1bb6bdb73a29d1e1bca295219002d","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
