{"sequence":60,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T05:01:01.578919131Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-c879c09f","body":"`src/cli/run.rs:269-273` assumes every bead in a milestone starts with `<milestone_id>.` when it filters `br ready --json`. That is false for valid milestones with explicit bead IDs, including the new fixture that uses `bead-e2e` (`src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:1062-1083`). Because `resume_controller()` relies on `has_ready_beads()` in the `selecting` and `blocked` states (`src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:791-804` and `src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:894-906`), those milestones will never be seen as having ready work after a restart and can get stranded in `blocked` or transition incorrectly. Scope readiness by the milestone’s planned bead set, not by a string-prefix heuristic.","dedup_key":"6d5853e275de9a388ca9c80cd4ae3da6125484db8a32b121ea018b0d87c22a3d","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
