{"sequence":79,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T05:37:47.619592342Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-8e1219a6","body":"Bug: the success-reconciliation flow closes and syncs the bead before the controller can durably settle into a resumable post-run state ([src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:142-167]). On resume, any `claimed`, `running`, or `reconciling` controller whose bead is already closed is treated as stale divergence and forced into `needs_operator` ([src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:806-812], [src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:844-847], [src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:876-879]). A crash anywhere in that normal close/sync/reconcile window therefore strands an otherwise idempotent success path behind manual intervention. Either move the controller into a dedicated resumable reconciliation state before `br close`/`br sync`, or relax resume validation so this post-close window can continue automatically.","dedup_key":"eda58da9a36c221b40abb370d8e6126693bb5561657de69814e60762969410cd","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":80,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T05:37:47.630678328Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-5703ce90","body":"Bug: duplicate completion syncs on the final bead are no longer idempotent. Both the CLI sync path and the daemon reconciliation path unconditionally try to re-enter `reconciling` for a completed run ([src/cli/run.rs:585-595], [src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:289-297]), but `sync_controller_task_reconciling` hard-errors once the controller has already reached `completed` ([src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:530-534]). Because successful final-bead reconciliation itself moves the controller to `completed` ([src/cli/run.rs:653-674], [src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:381-397]), rerunning `ralph-burning run sync-milestone` or replaying the same completed reconciliation becomes a hard failure instead of a no-op/repair.","dedup_key":"01e4a6f703e1cc50ab2b5bfea8252f09b65bdc37291d79de491e1ac54de9afee","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408030848","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
